Mumble is an open source, cross platform, low-latency, high quality voice over IP (VoIP) client. Mumble uses a client/server architecture and is primarily used by gamers, but can be used for any VoIP purpose.

== Installation ==

=== Kernel ===

Many laptops have built-in USB microphones (almost always paired with USB web cameras). The kernel needs the <var>SND_USB_AUDIO</var> symbol enabled to support USB audio (input) devices.

{{KernelBox|title=Enable support for <var>SND_USB_AUDIO</var>|1=
